results.post_message: April 15th, 2015 marked the beginning of a new annual Boston tradition: One Boston Day.  In the spirit of this day, the officers of the Bolton Police Department were honored by a Police Appreciation Day yesterday afternoon, coordinated by Bolton's Council on Aging. Seniors from Bolton stopped by to meet with some of our officers, and drop off numerous plates of baked goods as a way of saying thanks for the services our officers provide to the community, both on and off duty. We are truly humbled by such an outpouring of support and generosity, and give our sincerest and deepest thanks to those who organized and attended this event. Such gestures remind first responders, despite all the difficulties or awful things they have witnessed in their careers, of why they entered public service, and that their efforts don't go unnoticed. It was a true pleasure to meet and chat with all who came, and we will continue to serve our community with pride and professionalism.
